{"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc11-516-understanding-layout-and-gestures-in-safari-on-ios-and-lion"]}],"kind":"article","hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC11"]]},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC11-516-Understanding-Layout-and-Gestures-in-Safari-on-iOS-and-Lion","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"sections":[],"metadata":{"roleHeading":"WWDC11","role":"sampleCode","modules":[{"name":"WWDC Notes"}],"title":"Understanding Layout and Gestures in Safari on iOS and Lion"},"abstract":[{"text":"Safari on iOS was the first browser to deliver web content that responded to gestures such as panning, double-tapping, and pinching. Now, many of the basic principles behind gesture-friendly layout and gesture recognition have been carried over to Safari on Mac OS X Lion. See how to make web content that already looks great even better by learning the concepts behind gesture-enabled web layout.  Understand how scrollable content and fixed positioning works in zoom-able interfaces, learn best practices for handling overlay scrollbars, discover optimization that speed up back-forward navigation, and more.","type":"text"}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Overview","anchor":"overview","type":"heading","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"😱 “No Overview Available!”"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Be the hero to change that by watching the video or reading the transcript on WWDCIndex and providing notes! It’s super easy:"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing"}]}]}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"sampleCodeDownload":{"kind":"sampleDownload","action":{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier